## FDA "Intended Use" Doctrine

Under 21 CFR 201.128, a product becomes a "drug" if its intended use — inferred from labeling, advertising, and surrounding circumstances — is to diagnose, cure, treat, or prevent disease.

### What Triggers FDA Enforcement (From Actual Warning Letters)
- Health claims anywhere on the site, even subtle language
- Consumer-oriented dosing instructions
- RUO disclaimers contradicted by surrounding marketing content
- Social media posts implying human use
- Reconstitution or administration instructions
- Selling syringes alongside peptides
- Customer reviews containing health claims that vendor failed to moderate

### Criminal Prosecution Precedents
- Paradigm Peptides owner: guilty plea (Dec 2025)
- Tailor Made Compounding: guilty plea, $1.79M forfeiture, prison
- All American Peptide: guilty plea, $3M+ forfeitures
- 80+ FDA warning letters issued 2025-2026
- Peptide Sciences shut down March 6, 2026

