## ✅ SAFE Language

- "For laboratory research use only"
- "≥99% purity verified by third-party HPLC analysis"
- "Batch-specific Certificates of Analysis available"
- Molecular specifications (sequence, MW, CAS number)
- "Studied in preclinical literature"
- "Examined in in vitro and animal model systems"
- "Research compound with batch documentation"
- "Third-party analytical verification available per lot"
- Physical/chemical properties (solubility, stability, appearance)
- Storage and handling for laboratory context
- Published research citations with PubMed PMID numbers
- Mechanism descriptions: receptor binding, pathway modulation, signaling cascades

## ❌ PROHIBITED Language

Never use anywhere — not in copy, meta tags, alt text, schema markup, or code comments that render:

- Health benefits, therapeutic claims, physiological effects
- "healing" / "recovery" / "repair" (human context)
- "anti-aging" / "fat loss" / "weight loss" / "muscle growth"
- "dose" / "dosing" / "dosage" / "protocol" / "cycle" / "stack"
- "inject" / "injection" / "subcutaneous" / "intramuscular"
- "clinically proven" / "FDA approved" / "pharmaceutical grade"
- "treatment" / "therapy" / "patients" / "wellness"
- Before/after results or imagery
- Testimonials about outcomes or effects
- Reconstitution instructions implying human use
- "Generic version of [FDA-approved drug]"
- Any implication of human or animal consumption

